This will be a more succinct report due to increased containment and people getting power and internet access back. If you would like specific details about evacuations, fire activity, and/or weather, just ask me. 

(2/

#KincadeFire Overnight firefighting made considerable progress! There is still activity in the steep area near Cobb Mountain/The Geysers, which is a hard area to access due to the terrain and one lane roads, and Mt St Helena. 

(3/

#KincadeFire Stump holes and trees are still causing concerns. Some have fire or embers in them, some roll down hills and spread fire, etc. 

Mop up activities have started. That is when fire crews extinguish/remove burning material near control lines. 

(4/

#KincadeFire STRUCTURE STATUS
282 (increase from 266) destroyed, including 141 residential and 10 commercial

50 (up from 47)  damaged, including 33 residential and 1 commercial

INJURIES
4 first responders
